<FindBugsFilter xmlns="https://github.com/spotbugs/filter/3.0.0">
  <!--
    Reviewed suppressions (Chapter 16: suppress with a reason, never disable a whole detector).

    This capstone module has NONE: that is the chapter's point made by the assembled build. The gate's
    model types are immutable records (StageOutcome, GateLadder) and a sealed verdict of records
    (ShipVerdict), the stack view is stateless, and the gate itself holds only its ladder and two atomic
    counters, exposing no array or mutable collection — so the representation-exposure detectors stay
    quiet without any suppression. The filter is kept (empty) so a future, genuinely-reviewed
    suppression has a home with a reason rather than being added inline.
  -->
</FindBugsFilter>
